      • toVar

        public static java.lang.String toVar(byte[] arr)
        toVar method converts the input array (a0, a1, ...) to a monomial "b^(a1) c^(a2) d^(a3)...". The elements of the input array is the power of b, c, d,...,z. If the power is greater than nine then parenthesis will be added. Negative elements will be ignored. For example, if arr = [2, 1, 3, -1, 14] then output is "b^1 c^3 e^(14)" (with space between each monomial). Only the first 26 elements will be used.
        Parameters:
        arr - A byte array {a0, a1, a2...}
        Returns:
        The correponding monomial "b^(a1) c^(a2) d^(a3)...".
